        "additional_notes": "This question tests the understanding of inputs to Estimate Activity Resources, specifically focusing on which document provides the 'detailed technical requirements.' The Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) Dictionary is the definitive source for elaborated descriptions of the work packages, including their technical specifications. This level of detail is essential for precisely identifying the types and quantities of resources, such as specific cable types, networking equipment, and specialized technicians required. The other options are inputs or outputs from other processes that serve different purposes in planning. This is a difficult question because other documents are indeed inputs to other processes, but the WBS Dictionary provides the *technical specificity* needed here.",
