        "additional_notes": "This question probes the understanding of the logical flow of project planning processes. After estimating activity resources, the *most important next step* is to integrate these estimates into the schedule development process. Resource availability and types directly impact how activities can be sequenced and how long they will take. Without robust resource estimates, the schedule will be unrealistic. While other options might occur later (procurement, budget requests) or are continuous (communication), building the schedule is the direct and critical next logical step in defining the project execution plan. This is a difficult question because it requires understanding the downstream impact of one planning process on another.",
