        "concepts_to_understand": "The four types of dependencies: mandatory, discretionary, external, and internal. Understanding the source and implications of each dependency type is critical for effective schedule management, particularly for identifying areas of potential flexibility or constraint. Discretionary dependencies, often called 'soft logic,' are based on preferences or best practices and can be changed.",
