        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - Discretionary dependencies are based on best practices or preferences, whereas this is a rigid requirement imposed by an outside entity.",
        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - An external dependency is a relationship between project activities and non-project activities. In this case, the 'Environmental Impact Assessment' activity relies on 'external regulatory approval' from an entity outside the direct control of the project team, making it an external dependency.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - A resource-based dependency relates to the availability of specific resources. While resources might be needed for the assessment, the dependency is fundamentally on the external approval, not solely resource availability.",
