        "option_d_result": "CORRECT - A focus group is the most appropriate tool. It is a structured discussion with a pre-selected group of stakeholders to gather qualitative feedback on specific topics or concepts. The facilitator can guide the discussion to ensure all participants contribute, and the project manager can observe the group's reactions and dynamics, which is crucial for gauging public opinion on design options. It provides a controlled and efficient way to get in-depth feedback from a representative sample of the community.",
