        "suggested_read": "['PMBOK Guide, 6th Edition, Section 5.2.2.5', 'PMI Agile Practice Guide, Section 4.2.6']",
        "concepts_to_understand": "Focus groups are a versatile tool for gathering qualitative information from a target audience. They are particularly useful for testing concepts or designs and getting rich feedback in a time-efficient manner. They provide a middle ground between the depth of an interview and the breadth of a survey, making them a powerful tool for a project manager.",
