        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - A virtual brainstorming session would be difficult to facilitate with 50 representatives. It would be inefficient and hard to manage, and it is not the most effective way to collect specific, detailed requirements from each individual office. It is better for generating ideas than for gathering structured data.",
        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - While phone interviews are a possibility, conducting 50 individual interviews would be extremely time-consuming and inefficient. The project manager needs a tool that can gather standardized data from a large number of people at once. The scenario's constraints of '50 different branch offices' make interviews impractical.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - Facilitating 50 virtual focus groups would be even more time-consuming and resource-intensive than interviews. Focus groups are better for in-depth, qualitative feedback from a smaller group, not for collecting standardized information from a large, geographically diverse population.",
