        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - The Tornado Diagram is the standard visual output of a Sensitivity Analysis. It is a bar chart that shows the range of uncertainty for a single variable on the project objective, with the most impactful variable at the top. The length of the bar represents the magnitude of the impact, making it ideal for the project manager to visually show which variable (steel cost, labor cost, etc.) has the most significant effect on the project's NPV.",
