        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - What-if Scenario Analysis is the ideal technique for this situation. The project manager wants to specifically model a single, high-impact event ('what if the key government regulation changes?'). This analysis involves taking a specific set of assumptions (the doubled cost and six-month delay) and modeling its impact on the project's baselines to understand the potential outcomes. This is a classic application of the tool to prepare for and plan for a specific risk event.",
