      "question_pmp": "A project manager is leading a new software development project to build a customer relationship management (CRM) system. The business analyst has gathered an extensive list of requirements, including customer details, purchase history, and product information. To ensure that the database is designed efficiently and accurately reflects the relationships between these different data entities, what is the most appropriate next step for the project manager to instruct the business analyst to create?",
