        "additional_notes": "This difficult question is similar to the previous one but applies the concept to the risk management knowledge area. The core challenge is distinguishing between brainstorming tools (like mind mapping) and structuring/organizing tools (like an RBS or a pre-defined risk register). Both A and D are plausible tools for risk management, but they are used for structuring risks after they have been identified. Mind mapping (B) is the correct tool for the initial 'creative' and 'non-linear' identification phase. The question tests the candidate's ability to choose the right tool for the right stage of the project.",
