        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - Crashing is a schedule compression technique that involves adding resources to critical path activities to shorten their duration. The scenario requires a specific reduction in project duration (10 days) and mentions the critical path, making crashing a direct and appropriate solution. It is a more precise and effective technique for a fixed time reduction than fast-tracking, which often involves re-sequencing.",
