        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - Resource smoothing is a technique to keep resource usage at a consistent level, but it can't be used if it causes the project to exceed its deadline. Smoothing would be used if there was float available and no impact on the end date. The scenario states there is an impact.",
        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - This is the most appropriate action. The project manager has identified a problem (resource conflict) and a constraint (fixed deadline). Since the direct solution (resource leveling) is not acceptable, the project manager must engage the sponsor to find a creative solution, such as finding another resource (a good alternative) or using a schedule compression technique (crashing or fast-tracking). This is a professional and proactive response.",
