        "concepts_to_understand": "Rolling Wave Planning is a type of progressive elaboration where a project plan is developed in detail for the near term and at a high level for the long term. As the project progresses and more information becomes available, the later phases are planned in greater detail. This technique is especially useful for projects with high uncertainty or long durations, as it prevents a project manager from spending too much time and resources on details that may change.",
