        "additional_notes": "The key phrase in this scenario is 'visualize the sequence of events and decision points.' This is the exact purpose of a flowchart. It allows the project team to collaboratively map out the steps of a process and identify where things went wrong. For example, the flowchart might reveal that a crucial quality check was omitted or that a decision was made incorrectly at a specific point. While other options like a cause-and-effect diagram are also used in root cause analysis, they serve a different purpose (brainstorming causes, not mapping a process). The distinction between mapping a process (flowchart) and brainstorming causes (cause-and-effect) is a key concept to understand for the PMP exam. A flowchart helps the team understand the 'how' and 'where' of the problem, which is what the question is asking for.",
