        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - Design for Six Sigma is a structured methodology for designing products and processes that are robust and have high quality, but it's a specific approach and not the general term for incorporating a wide range of specific attributes like maintainability, manufacturability, or in this case, sanitization. DfX is the more encompassing and correct term.",
