        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - Design for Cost (DfC) focuses on optimizing the design to minimize material and production costs. While a valid DfX approach, it is too narrow for this scenario, which is primarily concerned with a non-cost-related attribute: the ability to be sanitized and sterilized for hospital use. The correct answer is the broader DfX methodology.",
