      "id": "1756654715623",
      "question_pmp": "A project manager is reviewing the risk register. Two risks are identified as high-impact and high-probability. Risk A is 'a critical technical component failing,' which requires a complex design change and a 3-month lead time for a new part. Risk B is 'a key supplier going bankrupt,' which has a clear, readily available alternate supplier. Which of the following is the BEST way to use Risk Urgency Assessment to decide which risk to prioritize?",
