        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - The Risk Urgency Assessment would reveal that Risk A is more urgent. While both are high-impact and high-probability, the 'urgency' of Risk A is higher because its response (a complex design change with a 3-month lead time) requires a long timeframe to implement. The project manager must begin planning for this response immediately to ensure it can be executed if the risk occurs. The response for Risk B can be implemented much more quickly, making it less urgent.",
