        "concepts_to_understand": "Monte Carlo Simulation is the most comprehensive quantitative risk analysis tool. It is used to model the overall project risk by considering the cumulative effect of multiple risks and their interactions. It provides a more realistic and complete picture of the project's overall risk exposure than other quantitative tools that focus on individual risks.",
        "additional_notes": "This question is a good test of the candidate's ability to select the correct tool for a specific purpose. The scenario's key phrase is 'model the combined effect of these risks.' Monte Carlo Simulation is the only tool that can do this. The distractors are all valid quantitative risk tools, but they are used for different purposes. The difficulty lies in understanding the specific use case for each tool and selecting the most appropriate one for the given problem.",
