        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - A procurement audit is a structured review of the procurement process and is performed after the contract has been completed. It is not part of the bidding process.",
        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - A Bidder Conference (also known as a pre-bid conference or pre-proposal conference) is a meeting held with all prospective sellers before they submit their proposals. The purpose is to ensure that all bidders have a clear and common understanding of the procurement requirements and to answer any questions in a fair and transparent manner.",
