        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - The project manager has a 'statistical relationship' (average cost per feature) and a clear metric (number of features, 20% more). This is the definition of 'Parametric Estimating.' It is a form of top-down estimating that is more accurate than analogous estimating because it uses a quantifiable relationship to calculate the cost. The project manager can use the cost per feature to adjust the previous project's estimate to account for the new features.",
