        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - The project manager has two quantifiable variables to work with: a 20% increase in scope and a 10% increase in developer cost. 'Parametric Estimating' is the most appropriate technique for this scenario, as it uses a statistical relationship to create a more accurate estimate. The project manager can use the previous project's cost as a baseline and then adjust it based on the two known variables, providing a more reliable estimate than a simple analogous estimate.",
