        "additional_notes": "This question is designed to test the nuanced distinction between Analogous and Parametric Estimating, which is a common point of confusion. The presence of quantifiable changes ('20% smaller,' '10% cost increase') is the key to identifying that Parametric Estimating is the more appropriate choice. A simple Analogous estimate would ignore these crucial details. The correct answer highlights the value of using all available information to create the most accurate estimate possible.",
