        "additional_notes": "This question tests the project manager's understanding of the importance of backlog refinement in the agile framework. The scenario is a classic example of a product owner bringing an unrefined user story to the team. The correct action is to enforce the process of backlog refinement, which ensures the team is only working on items that are well-defined and ready to be worked on. The incorrect options represent common agile anti-patterns that would lead to project failure.",
