        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - A non-disclosure agreement (NDA) is a legal contract that establishes confidentiality between two or more parties. While it may be used in conjunction with other documents, its primary purpose is to protect sensitive information, not to outline the overall collaborative framework.",
