        "suggested_read": "['PMBOK® Guide, 7th Edition: 3.5 Project Artifacts', 'PMBOK® Guide, 6th Edition: 13.1.3.1 Stakeholder Register']",
        "concepts_to_understand": "The Stakeholder Register is a living document. The process of identifying and analyzing stakeholders is iterative and should continue throughout the project. The information recorded in the register, such as a stakeholder's influence, interest, and engagement level, can and will change. Project managers must be vigilant in monitoring these changes and updating the register to maintain an accurate and effective stakeholder management strategy.",
        "additional_notes": "This question tests the iterative nature of the 'Identify Stakeholders' and 'Monitor Stakeholder Engagement' processes. The project manager's role is to ensure that project artifacts are accurate and up-to-date. The most direct and responsible action is to update the Stakeholder Register, which is the repository for this specific type of information. The other options are either incorrect project management practices (ignoring the change), using the wrong document (Issue Log), or are premature (escalating to the sponsor).",
