        "additional_notes": "This question tests the candidate's understanding of the strategic application of a Story Map. The scenario places the project manager and product owner in a decision-making role for the first release. The correct answer, building a 'walking skeleton,' is the textbook agile approach to this problem. It is the most effective way to get early, end-to-end feedback on the product's core functionality. The other options are plausible but either violate core agile principles (A, D) or are a poor prioritization strategy (C). The question is 'difficult' because it requires the candidate to understand not just what a Story Map is, but how it is used to make a critical strategic decision about product delivery.",
