        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - A stakeholder engagement plan is for managing communications and expectations. While it can help to get stakeholder buy-in, it does not provide the team with the transparent, data-driven prioritization model that they need to understand why certain features are being prioritized. It addresses the 'who' and 'how' of communication, not the 'why' of prioritization.",
        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - The core problem is a lack of transparency in the prioritization process. A Risk-Adjusted Backlog directly addresses this problem. By scoring each feature on its business value, risk, and effort, the project manager and the product owner can create a transparent and objective prioritization model. This allows the team to see 'why' certain features are being prioritized and provides a shared understanding and a more realistic plan. This is the most effective tool to address the root cause of the team's pushback.",
