      "question_pmp": "A project manager is leading an agile team. The team has a product backlog that is prioritized by business value. The product owner is concerned that the team is only addressing the highest-value features and is ignoring a low-value, high-risk technical debt item that could have a significant negative impact on the project's long-term sustainability. The project manager wants to convince the product owner to address this item. What is the BEST approach to use a Risk-Adjusted Backlog to justify prioritizing this item?",
