        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - Risk mitigation is a proactive risk response strategy that aims to reduce the probability and/or the impact of a negative risk (a threat). By adding a risk mitigation activity to the schedule, the project manager is implementing a plan to proactively reduce the overall project risk. The goal is to bring the risk to an acceptable level. This is the primary purpose of a risk mitigation activity and is what a Risk Burn Down Chart is designed to track.",
