        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - A Service Level Agreement (SLA) is the most appropriate document. It is a legally binding agreement that defines the level of service, quality, and performance that a vendor is committed to providing. It specifically addresses metrics such as system uptime, response times, and other performance guarantees.",
